<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1808,2023]" box="[151,1435,1808,1831]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1808,1831]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">1. Thorax entirely black .................................................................................................................................................. 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1808,2023]" box="[151,1435,1840,1863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1840,1863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">– Thorax predominantly yellow ..................................................................................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1808,2023]" box="[151,1435,1872,1896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1872,1896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
2. Abdomen entirely black; one pair of scutellar setae; male and female terminalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[1112,1174,1872,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,254,1775,1799]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,274,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-113@5.[151,1436,274,1750]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Macrostomus fusciventris, n. sp., paratypes from Acre. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F, female wing. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; EP, epandrium; PC, posterior cercus; T8, tergite 8; ST8, sternite 8. Scales: A = 0.5 mm; B,C,E–G = 0.2 mm; D,H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321578" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321578/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
<emphasis box="[1179,1363,1872,1895]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1204,1363,1872,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusciventris" status="n. sp.">M. fusciventris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1376,1435,1872,1896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1376,1435,1872,1896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1808,2023]" box="[151,1435,1904,1927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1904,1927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">– Abdomen yellow or yellowish red; usually two pairs of scutellar setae ...................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1808,2023]" box="[151,1435,1936,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1936,1959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">3. Postcranium yellow ventrally ...................................................................................................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1808,2023]" box="[151,1435,1968,1991]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1968,1991]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">– Postcranium entirely black .......................................................................................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1808,2023]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<keyLead lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<keyStep lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
4. First hind tarsomere with two slender setae dorsally; male and female wings elongated (
<figureCitation box="[1171,1279,2000,2023]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Figs. 4a,f</figureCitation>
); female wing entirely brown infuscated, sinuose along anal margin (
<figureCitation box="[784,857,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 4f</figureCitation>
); male terminalia with elongate distally bifid anterior cercus and posterior cercus with simple incurved protuberance (
<figureCitation box="[879,986,184,207]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,254,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[171,1424,339,1739]" captionTargetId="figure-149@8.[151,1436,335,1757]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Macrostomus longipennis, n. sp., paratypes. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–I, female; F, wing; G, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; H, tergite 8, dorsal view; I, genital fork. Scales: B,C,E,G,H = 0.2 mm; D,I = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321584/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Figs. 4c,d</figureCitation>
); female hind tibia without pinnate scales 
<emphasis box="[206,1363,216,239]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
..................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1203,1363,216,239]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis" status="n. sp.">M. longipennis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1376,1436,215,239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1376,1436,215,239]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
– First hind tarsomere with seven slender setae dorsally; male wing not so elongated, almost entirely hyaline; male terminalia as in figures 20–22 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael &amp; Cumming" box="[528,820,280,303]" firstAuthor="Rafael" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="49 - 64" refId="ref9495" refString="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2006) New species of Macrostomus Wiedemann (Diptera, Empididae) from Colombia, Ecuador and Peru. Zootaxa 1136, 49 - 64." type="journal article" year="2006">Rafael &amp; Cumming (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, with anterior cercus stouter and posterior cercus without incurved protuberance; female unknown .............................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" box="[1054,1435,312,335]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[1054,1219,312,335]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">M. occidentalis</emphasis>
Rafael &amp; Cumming
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
<key pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" box="[151,1435,344,367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,344,367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">5. Postcranium shining black with no pruinescence on upper third ................................................................................ 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" box="[151,1435,376,399]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,376,399]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">– Postcranium black but entirely gray pruinose............................................................................................................... 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
6. Male tergite 8 acute distally (
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael &amp; Cumming" box="[531,812,408,431]" firstAuthor="Rafael" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="439 - 448" refId="ref9452" refString="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2004). The Neotropical genera Macrostomus Wiedemann and Porphyrochroa Melander (Diptera, Empididae, Empidinae). Revista brasileira de Zoologia 21, 439 - 448." type="journal article" year="2004">Rafael &amp; Cumming 2004</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 5); male frons very narrow, about one third anterior ocellus width; supra-alar presutural setae absent; first hind tarsomere with 1–3 slender setae; female hind tibia without pinnate scales ................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[1154,1436,472,495]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis box="[1154,1312,472,495]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
– Male tergite 8 with distal protuberance truncated (
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael" box="[751,887,504,527]" firstAuthor="Rafael" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="127 - 132" refId="ref9412" refString="Rafael, J. A. (2001). Redescricao de duas especies neotropicais de Empididae (Diptera) descritas por Curran e revalidacao do genero Porphyrochroa. Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 90, 127 - 132." type="journal article" year="2001">Rafael 2001</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3); male frons wider, about one half to three quarters anterior ocellus width; one pair of supra-alar presutural setae present; first hind tarsomere with 4–5 slender setae; female hind tibia with pinnate scales on dorsal and ventral surfaces (
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael" box="[995,1128,568,591]" firstAuthor="Rafael" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" pagination="127 - 132" refId="ref9412" refString="Rafael, J. A. (2001). Redescricao de duas especies neotropicais de Empididae (Diptera) descritas por Curran e revalidacao do genero Porphyrochroa. Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 90, 127 - 132." type="journal article" year="2001">Rafael 2001</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 4).................................. ................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Curran)" baseAuthorityName="Curran" box="[1185,1435,600,623]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvithorax">
<emphasis box="[1185,1337,600,623]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">M. fulvithorax</emphasis>
(Curran)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
7. Male tergite 8 forked distally (
<figureCitation box="[526,606,632,655]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 5b</figureCitation>
); female hind tibia with pinnate scales on dorsal surface as well as basal third ventrally ............................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1241,1362,664,687]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcatus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1241,1362,664,687]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">M. furcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1376,1435,663,687]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1376,1435,663,687]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
– Male tergite 8 with apex truncated, not forked (
<figureCitation box="[704,783,696,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,255,1698,1722]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,296,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-189@12.[151,1436,274,1672]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrostomus flavus, n. sp., paratypes from Roraima. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–L, female; F, hindleg, posterior view; G, wing; H, distal abdominal tergites, dorsal view with right setae omitted; I, distal abdominal segments, lateral view; J, distal abdominal sternites, ventral view with left setae omitted; K–L, genital fork in lateral and ventral view; M, spermathecae. Scales: F = 0.5 mm; B–C,E,H–J = 0.2 mm; K–M = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321590/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 6b</figureCitation>
); female hind tibia with pinnate scales only on dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[207,280,728,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,255,1698,1722]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,296,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-189@12.[151,1436,274,1672]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrostomus flavus, n. sp., paratypes from Roraima. A–E, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. F–L, female; F, hindleg, posterior view; G, wing; H, distal abdominal tergites, dorsal view with right setae omitted; I, distal abdominal segments, lateral view; J, distal abdominal sternites, ventral view with left setae omitted; K–L, genital fork in lateral and ventral view; M, spermathecae. Scales: F = 0.5 mm; B–C,E,H–J = 0.2 mm; K–M = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321590/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Fig. 6f</figureCitation>
) ................................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityYear="2009" box="[1263,1363,728,751]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1263,1363,728,751]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">M. flavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1376,1436,727,751]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1376,1436,727,751]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
8. CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[257,264,774,787]" fontSize="5" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">1</subScript>
vein shorter than dm-cu vein (
